r>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 8:19:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1978.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Flaming without cause</span><hr size=1> I think the Wimbus threads and also threads having concerned my own guild members is highlighting a problem on this message board.<br>
<br>
Something I hate:<br>
Sad, weak people writing lame posts attempting to ruin the reputation of another player on a message board they may or may not even read.<br>
<br>
I for one am instantly suspicious of anyone posting about another player giving their names.  Especially if the other party is not there to defend themselves.<br>
<br>
So, I know most of you dont care, but flame without cause and you'll find me adding you to my 'sad gimp' list of people to ignore in game.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Baldisking 'Guilddestroyer' Rugisbad, Season 52 Pathfinder <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twotribes>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 623<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 12:48:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1978.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Flaming without cause</span><hr size=1> So posting someones name is automaticly without cause?<br>
<br>
I personally dont see the point of posting a flame against someone if they dont read the board. Kind of a waste of time and effort.<br>
<br>
There are times I want a name attached to an act. In case I choose to venture forth much in FV, it is nice to know who to avoid. I am not one of the people that instantly assumes someone is lieing when they post a name. We have a few of those, they will champion ANYONE that gets named for any offensive no matter how damning the evidence or number of people that tell you it happened. Just curious when you think naming is acceptable? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeldagisravensoul>Zeldagis Ravensoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nearly invisible,<br> Totally Moronic</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 1:15:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1978.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Flaming without cause</span><hr size=1> I think whining on the boards about someone's actions in and of itself is lame.  I'll join in the flamefest of a person who did something stupid (Yar :P ), but I do it for fun and enjoyment, not some sort of &quot;boy, I can now avoid that person&quot;.  Call me shallow, but coming to this board to whine about someone else's actions only shows me that you aren't mature enough to handle the matter yourself (of course there are exceptions, like trade scams, ect).  I also don't think you should petition unless it's bug related.  There really are few times you actually need to petition anything, most of the time the situation can be resolved, but a lot of people are too lazy to take the time to do it.  It's easier to /report and /petition.  To me, thats the same as running home to mommy and daddy.<br>
<br>
In short, there are too many hall monitors on this board, but that's the nature of it.  I accept it as it is and have fun mocking and ridiculing others.  I guess I'm easily amused.<br>
<br>
As to naming names, it adds to the stupidity on the board, so therefore it should stay.  In a perfect world, people would suck it up and figure it out themselves, this board is proof that the world ain't close to perfect.<br>
<br>
