<br>
* Its tongue in cheek, humourous and in no way intended offensively (about the only time I'll post names).<br>
* I do it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (normally for the above reason)<br>
* The person is a known poster here and can defend themselves. Even then its lame, why not sort it out in game?<br>
<br>
I just see calling out names here is akin to a schoolboy running to a teacher saying 'miiiiiiisssss, miiiiiissss,  was nasty to me miiiiiisssss'.  Saying that ..... its what politicians do in RL <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ansurfv>AnsurFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 2:46:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1978.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Flaming without cause</span><hr size=1> There are some people in the game who you cannot resolve issues with. Like it or not, sometimes there is a RL jerk behind the keyboard. I ran into someone in HK that refused to respect our camp. I did a search and contacted a higher member of his guild who then contacted him. He would not even answer the tells from his guild member, but he did suddenly decide to move elsewhere. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I have met other members of this guild that were very nice. I won't name him this time because the older guild member was very nice and polite, even asked me to extend his apology to the rest of my group. But if this situation had persisted and the other guild member had ben nonchalant or rude then I would post both his name and guild here. <br>
It's not an unreasonable flame if Ansur (that's me) is running around pulling from your camp and being rude, to come here and say it (assuming you have already tried to resolve it ingame). Good or bad, a reputation is usually earned. Anyone who has met me ingame and dealt or grouped with me is welcome to mention my name on this board.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ettenok>EtteNoK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 10:02:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1978.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Flaming without cause</span><hr size=1> I like losing battles =) but this one's too far for me, I have to /agree with these people there are times posting a name could definately come in handy =D<br>
<br>
lmao liked yer second reason for a good time to post a name =D But going by yer rules, then if it's me doin it it's just fine =D But what about, oh like the feller with the trade window bit? or d'ya consider that a scam? hehe =D <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maritzia>Maritzia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Uptight Cleric</span><br>  Posts: 675<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/02 5:58:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1978.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Flaming without cause</span><hr size=1> Some of us like hearing about jerks in-game so we can avoid them.  I'm not going to avoid someone for one notice, but if someone posts here, and then 5 others jump in and describe other similar events, it kind of tells you something about that player.  Quite a few times someone has posted about someone, and within an hour, several others have added their &quot;hey, yeah, he did that to me to&quot;'s.<br>
<br>
That's the nice thing about this server, we stick up for each other and try and help each other out.  That's the main reason people post what some people call whining.  Not to whine, but to inform.<br>
<br>
Contrary to public opinion, most of us do not make a snap judgement based on one negative post here.  It is when we see a pattern of behavior that opinions are truly formed.<br>
<br>
 <p>Maritzia<br>
Cleric of Innoruk<br>
Serving Hate for 13 seasons</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=idril01>idril01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/02 7:26:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1978.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Flaming without cause</span><hr size=1> The soap box serves a variety of purposes.<br>
<br>
This is the kind of story we like to see here:<br>
<br>
A person, whom we will call, for rhetorical purposes, by the d00d name Poptart Megafart, does something bad (like, say, intentionally training).  Poptart responds to your polite requests to stop with a big steaming FU!  Newb001 (the one trained) contact's Poptart's guild, and seeks a resolution.  Poptart's guild responds with a big steaming FU!  Newb001 then petitions, spends 3 hours waiting for a GM, who finally responds with &quot;sorry, didn't see it can't help you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Newb001 then comes to this board and states their beef, whereupon the FV community fans the flames and eat's popcorn.  <br>
<br>
Poptart Megafart then comes here and points out that Newb001 is a total lamer and a newb loser so no one should believe him and since Poptart is level 57 and a 9/16ths, and since he needs a fungi and a foot rub he was totally justified in training Newb001 on 8 seperate occasions and the entire FV community is just flaming him because they are jealous of his short sword of the ykesha.<br>
<br>
Whereupon Poptart's guild comes to the Soapbox to point out that Newb001 is a total lamer who consorts with Al Queda and that no one should believe him and he's just trying to sully their image and that the other people who posted about the 6 other incidents of intential training are just jealous because Poptart's up and coming uberguild just took out Fippy Darkpaw and didn't share the phat lewtz.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, while the above story is silly, all too often actual events posted here often mirror it.  Do disgruntled people come here to extract their pound of flesh, and in the process sully the good name of honorable guilds?  Of course.<br>
<br>
But something tells me that, at least on occasion, some people who are in fact at fault come here and whine about the fact that someone had the cajones to stick their name, or the name of their guild, out here in public where the community can judge their actions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maladominus>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ak'Anon Sex Symbol</span><br>  Posts: 1038<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/02 7:48:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1978.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  bapsmear, a new word</span><hr size=1> I decided that today I would invent a new word. <br>
